.TH NIX-COPY-AS 1 "2025" "nix-copy-as" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nix-copy-as \- copy Nix store paths to a remote host via nix-serve
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nix-copy-as
.RB [ OPTIONS ]
.IR INSTALLABLE ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nix-copy-as
emulates "nix copy \-\-to" but works around signature checking by using nix-serve as a temporary substituter. It builds installables locally, starts a temporary nix-serve instance, and uses SSH port forwarding to make the built paths available to the remote machine as a substituter.
.PP
This is useful when copying store paths to a remote machine where you want them installed as a different user (via \-\-trusted-user) or when signature checking needs to be bypassed.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Required Options"
.TP
.BI "\-\-to " "[USERNAME@]HOST"
SSH username and host to connect to. The remote must be reachable via SSH.
.SS "Optional Options"
.TP
.BI "\-\-trusted-user " "USERNAME"
Run as this user on the remote machine. The user should be in the trusted-users list (see 'nix show-config trusted-users'). If not specified, runs as the SSH user.
.TP
.B \-\-no-check-sigs
Disable signature checking on the remote when copying store paths.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output. Passed to nix build and affects nix-serve output.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.SS "Nix Evaluation Options"
The following Nix evaluation options are passed through to 'nix build':
.TP
.BI "\-\-arg " "NAME VALUE"
Pass argument to Nix expression.
.TP
.BI "\-\-arg-from-file " "NAME PATH"
Pass argument from file to Nix expression.
.TP
.BI "\-\-argstr " "NAME VALUE"
Pass string argument to Nix expression.
.TP
.BI "\-\-arg-from-stdin " "NAME"
Pass argument from stdin to Nix expression.
.TP
.BI "\-\-eval-store " "URI"
Evaluation store URI.
.TP
.BI "\-I " "PATH"
.TQ
.BI "\-\-include " "PATH"
Add path to Nix search path.
.SS "Flake Options"
.TP
.BI "\-\-override-flake " "FLAKE-URL OVERRIDE"
Override a flake input.
.TP
.BI "\-\-override-input " "INPUT OVERRIDE"
Override a flake input.
.TP
.BI "\-\-inputs-from " "FLAKE"
Copy flake inputs from another flake.
.TP
.BI "\-\-output-lock-file " "PATH"
Write the lock file to a different path.
.TP
.BI "\-\-reference-lock-file " "PATH"
Read lock file from path.
.TP
.BI "\-\-update-input " "INPUT"
Update a specific flake input.
.TP
.B \-\-commit-lock-file
Commit changes to flake.lock.
.TP
.B \-\-no-registries
Don't use flake registries.
.TP
.B \-\-no-update-lock-file
Don't update flake.lock.
.TP
.B \-\-no-write-lock-file
Don't write flake.lock.
.TP
.B \-\-recreate-lock-file
Recreate flake.lock from scratch.
.TP
.B \-\-debugger
Start Nix debugger on evaluation errors.
.TP
.B \-\-impure
Allow impure expressions.
.SS "Logging Options"
.TP
.BI "\-\-log-format " "FORMAT"
Set log format (raw, raw-with-logs, internal-json, bar, bar-with-logs).
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Enable debug output.
.TP
.BR \-L ", " \-\-print-build-logs
Print full build logs on stderr.
.TP
.B \-\-quiet
Decrease verbosity.
.SH HOW IT WORKS
.B nix-copy-as
works by:
.PP
.IP 1. 4
Building the installable(s) locally using nom (nix-output-monitor).
.IP 2. 4
Finding a free port (starting at 5001) and starting nix-serve locally.
.IP 3. 4
Using SSH port forwarding to make the nix-serve available on the remote machine.
.IP 4. 4
Running 'nix build' on the remote using the forwarded port as a substituter, which copies the store paths.
.SH EXAMPLES
Copy the hello package from nixpkgs to a remote host:
.PP
.RS
.nf
nix-copy-as \-\-to user@remote-host nixpkgs#hello
.fi
.RE
.PP
Copy a local package without signature checking:
.PP
.RS
.nf
nix-copy-as \-\-to user@remote-host \-\-no-check-sigs .#mypackage
.fi
.RE
.PP
Copy and install as a trusted user on the remote:
.PP
.RS
.nf
nix-copy-as \-\-to user@remote-host \-\-trusted-user nixuser .#myapp
.fi
.RE
.PP
Copy with additional Nix arguments:
.PP
.RS
.nf
nix-copy-as \-\-to user@remote \-\-impure \-\-argstr version "1.2.3" .#app
.fi
.RE
